{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841356265,"sessionID":"ses_2879dcf1effe8NzjFZahhxooEQ","part":{"id":"prt_d78624785001On0vpxLqbbUuy0","messageID":"msg_d78623cbd0018zFQ4JxKTVqlKx","sessionID":"ses_2879dcf1effe8NzjFZahhxooEQ","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_3faa9faac2a44eb18b254160","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project at /home/dsj/benchmark to understand:\n1. What is PicoD? Search for any references to \"picod\", \"PicoD\", \"pico\" in the codebase\n2. Look at the pkg/ directory structure\n3. Check if there's already a pkg/picod directory\n4. Look for any existing specs, requirements, or documentation about file management\n5. Check for any OpenSpec or spec files in the repo\n6. Look at existing API patterns in the project\n\nReturn all findings including file paths and relevant code snippets.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2879dac9bffeOPEc62Ua3Wac17 (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive picture of the agentcube project. Here is my complete findings report:\n\n---\n\n## 1. What is PicoD?\n\n**PicoD** is a lightweight HTTP command execution and file management daemon that runs inside each sandbox Pod in the AgentCube platform. It is a core component of the AgentCube code execution capability.\n\n**Key characteristics:**\n- Receives JWT-authenticated HTTP requests\n- Executes commands within a configurable workspace jail (sandboxed directory)\n- Manages workspace files (upload, download, list, read, write, delete, etc.)\n- Exposes a health check endpoint\n- Uses RSA public key authentication (JWT RS256)\n\n**Architecture position:**\n```\nClient / SDK / CLI\n  -> Router (Deployment :8080)\n     -> WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n        -> K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)   <-- PicoD runs here\n```\n\n**AuthMode constant** defined at:\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` (line 13):\n```go\nAuthModePicoD AuthModeType = \"picod\"\nAuthModeNone  AuthModeType = \"none\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. pkg/ Directory Structure\n\nThe full `pkg/` directory in the target workspace:\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ apis/runtime/v1alpha1/       ŌĆö CRD type definitions\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ agent_type.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ codeinterpreter_types.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ constants.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ doc.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ groupversion_info.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ shared_types.go\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ zz_generated.deepcopy.go\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ common/types/                ŌĆö Shared types\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ types.go\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ picod/                       ŌĆö PicoD daemon (AR-015 implemented)\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ auth.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ config.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ execute.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ files.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ server.go\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ types.go\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ router/                      ŌĆö HTTP Router service\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ backend.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ config.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ errors.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ health.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ informer.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ jwt.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ loadbalancer.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ middleware.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ proxy.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ router.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ server.go\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ session_manager.go\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ store/                       ŌĆö Redis/Valkey session store\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ codec.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ singleton.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ store.go\nŌöé   Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ store_redis.go\nŌöé   ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ store_valkey.go\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆ workloadmanager/             ŌĆö Workload management\n    Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ handler/\n    Ōö£ŌöĆŌöĆ reconciler/\n    ŌööŌöĆŌöĆ response/\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. pkg/picod Directory -- EXISTS and Has Code\n\n**Yes, `pkg/picod/` already exists** with the following files:\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/types.go` | 51 | Request/Response structs, constants |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/config.go` | 20 | Config struct, CLI flag parsing |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/auth.go` | 111 | AuthManager, JWT middleware, key loading |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/server.go` | 88 | Server struct, NewServer, Run, route registration |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/execute.go` | 108 | ExecuteHandler, command execution logic |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files.go` | 339 | Upload/List/Download handlers, path sanitization |\n\n**Test files also exist:**\n- `auth_test.go`, `config_test.go`, `execute_test.go`, `health_test.go`, `sanitize_test.go`, `server_test.go`\n\n**Note:** There is NO `pkg/picod/files/` subdirectory yet -- AR-016 proposes creating one.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing Specs, Requirements, and Documentation About File Management\n\n### Primary spec files:\n\n**`/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/code-execution/spec.md`** (179 lines)\n- The base specification for PicoD\n- Covers: Command execution API, File upload API (multipart + JSON Base64), File listing API, File download API, Health endpoint, JWT authentication, Server configuration\n- Uses Gherkin-style scenarios (GIVEN/WHEN/THEN)\n\n**`/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md`** (490 lines)\n- AR-015 delta spec with detailed Gherkin scenarios\n- Covers all current PicoD endpoints with exhaustive test scenarios\n- Includes path sanitization algorithm specification\n\n### AR-015 (PicoD Command Execution API) -- IMPLEMENTED:\n\n**`/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-015/proposal.md`** (178 lines)\n- Fully detailed proposal with scope, architecture, impact analysis, risk assessment, alternatives, implementationĶ”üńé╣, and acceptance criteria\n- Current routes:\n  | Method | Path | Auth | Handler |\n  |--------|------|------|---------|\n  | GET | `/health` | None | HealthCheckHandler |\n  | POST | `/api/execute` | JWT | ExecuteHandler |\n  | POST | `/api/files` | JWT | UploadFileHandler |\n  | GET | `/api/files?path=` | JWT | ListFilesHandler |\n  | GET | `/api/files/*path` | JWT | DownloadFileHandler |\n\n**`/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-015/design.md`** (74 lines)\n- Skeleton template with TODOs (not filled in)\n\n### AR-016 (PicoD File Management API) -- NOT YET IMPLEMENTED:\n\n**`/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-016/proposal.md`** (218 lines)\n- Fully detailed proposal building on AR-015\n- Proposes extending file management with: ReadFile (offset/limit), WriteFile (offset/append), StatFile, BatchDelete, BatchMove, chunked transfer, CreateDirectory, SearchFiles (glob), Chmod\n- Proposes refactoring `files.go` into `files/` subpackage\n- Proposed new routes:\n  | Method | Path | Auth | Handler |\n  |--------|------|------|---------|\n  | POST | `/api/files/read` | JWT | ReadFileHandler |\n  | POST | `/api/files/write` | JWT | WriteFileHandler |\n  | GET | `/api/files/stat?path=` | JWT | StatFileHandler |\n  | GET | `/api/files?path=` | JWT | ListFilesHandler (migrated) |\n  | POST | `/api/files/upload` | JWT | UploadFileHandler (migrated) |\n  | GET | `/api/files/download?path=` | JWT | DownloadFileHandler (migrated) |\n  | POST | `/api/files/delete` | JWT | DeleteFileHandler |\n  | POST | `/api/files/move` | JWT | MoveFileHandler |\n  | POST | `/api/files/mkdir` | JWT | MkDirHandler |\n  | POST | `/api/files/search` | JWT | SearchFilesHandler |\n  | POST | `/api/files/chmod` | JWT | ChmodHandler |\n\n**`/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-016/design.md`** (74 lines)\n- Skeleton template with TODOs (not filled in)\n\n**`/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-016/tasks.md`** (23 lines)\n- Skeleton with TODOs (not filled in)\n\n---\n\n## 5. OpenSpec / Spec Files in the Repo\n\n**No OpenSpec directory found** (searched for `**/openspec*/**` and `**/*SPEC*` -- no results).\n\n**However**, the project follows an OpenSpec-like convention with specs organized by domain:\n\n**`/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/`** directory contains:\n```\nspecs/\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ ci-cd/spec.md\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ cli-toolkit/spec.md\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ code-execution/spec.md       <-- PicoD spec\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ deployment/spec.md\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ idle-cleanup/spec.md\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ integrations/spec.md\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ project.md\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ python-sdk/spec.md\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ sandbox-orchestration/spec.md\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ session-routing/spec.md\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ session-store/spec.md\nŌö£ŌöĆŌöĆ test_spec.md\nŌööŌöĆŌöĆ testing/\n```\n\n**Project context file:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/project.md` -- titled \"AgentCube -- OpenSpec Project Context\"\n\n**Change Request (AR) pattern:**\n- Each AR has: `proposal.md`, `design.md`, `tasks.md`\n- 16 ARs exist: AR-001 through AR-016\n- AR-015 = PicoD Command Execution API (implemented)\n- AR-016 = PicoD File Management API (proposed, not implemented)\n\n---\n\n## 6. Existing API Patterns in the Project\n\n### Pattern 1: PicoD Server (pkg/picod/) -- Simple inline handlers\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/server.go`\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    engine       *gin.Engine\n    config       Config\n    authManager  *AuthManager\n    startTime    time.Time\n    workspaceDir string\n}\n\nfunc (s *Server) registerRoutes() {\n    api := s.engine.Group(\"/api\")\n    api.Use(s.authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n    {\n        api.POST(\"/execute\", s.ExecuteHandler)\n        api.POST(\"/files\", s.UploadFileHandler)\n        api.GET(\"/files\", s.ListFilesHandler)\n        api.GET(\"/files/*path\", s.DownloadFileHandler)\n    }\n    s.engine.GET(\"/health\", s.HealthCheckHandler)\n}\n```\n\nHandlers are methods on `*Server` directly, all in flat files within the package.\n\n### Pattern 2: Router Server (pkg/router/) -- Structured with separate concerns\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/server.go`\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    config         *Config\n    engine         *gin.Engine\n    httpServer     *http.Server\n    sessionManager SessionManager\n    storeClient    store.Store\n    httpTransport  *http.Transport\n    jwtManager     *JWTManager\n}\n```\n\nUses middleware chain: `AuthMiddleware` + `ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware` on `/v1` group.\n\n### Pattern 3: WorkloadManager Handlers (pkg/workloadmanager/handler/) -- Dependency injection\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_create.go`\n```go\ntype SandboxCreateHandlerDeps struct {\n    DynamicClient     dynamic.Interface\n    Clientset         clientset.Interface\n    KubeClientset     kubernetes.Interface\n    InformerFactory   externalversions.SharedInformerFactory\n    Store             Store\n    Reconciler        SandboxReconcilerWatcher\n    TokenCache        TokenCache\n    UserClientFactory UserClientFactory\n    EnableAuth        bool\n}\n\ntype SandboxCreateHandler struct { ... }\n\nfunc NewSandboxCreateHandler(deps *SandboxCreateHandlerDeps) *SandboxCreateHandler { ... }\n```\n\nUses a `Deps` struct pattern for dependency injection, with a separate `response` package for standardized responses.\n\n### Pattern 4: Response helpers (pkg/workloadmanager/response/)\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/response/response.go`\n```go\ntype SuccessResponse struct {\n    Data    interface{} `json:\"data\"`\n    Message string      `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype ErrorResponse struct {\n    Error     string `json:\"error\"`\n    Code      int    `json:\"code\"`\n    RequestID string `json:\"request_id,omitempty\"`\n}\n\nfunc JSON(c *gin.Context, code int, data interface{}) { ... }\nfunc Error(c *gin.Context, httpCode int, code int, message string) { ... }\n```\n\n### PicoD Error Response Pattern (current)\n\nPicoD currently uses inline `gin.H` responses:\n```go\nc.JSON(http.StatusBadRequest, gin.H{\n    \"error\": \"Missing 'path' query parameter\",\n    \"code\":  http.StatusBadRequest,\n})\n```\n\n### Entry Point Pattern\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/picod/main.go`\n```go\nfunc main() {\n    klog.InitFlags(nil)\n    config := picod.ParseFlags()\n    server := picod.NewServer(config)\n    if err := server.Run(); err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"server failed: %v\", err)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Question | Finding |\n|----------|---------|\n| What is PicoD? | Lightweight HTTP daemon for command execution + file management inside sandbox pods |\n| pkg/ structure | 6 top-level packages: apis, common, picod, router, store, workloadmanager |\n| pkg/picod exists? | **Yes** -- 6 Go source files + 6 test files (AR-015 implemented) |\n| pkg/picod/files/ exists? | **No** -- AR-016 proposes creating this subpackage |\n| File management specs | `specs/code-execution/spec.md` (base), `delta-spec.md` (AR-015 detailed), `changes/AR-016/proposal.md` (AR-016 extended) |\n| OpenSpec files | No OpenSpec directory; specs live in `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/` with domain subdirectories |\n| API patterns | Gin-based, JWT-protected `/api` group, handlers as Server methods, inline `gin.H` error responses |\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2879dac9bffeOPEc62Ua3Wac17","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775841203042,"end":1775841356262}}}}
